Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.07,0:03:47.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但认真地说 不要跳着看这个视频\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}But seriously, don't skip through this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.02,0:03:49.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你会震惊于我所了解到的一些东西\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}You'll be shocked at some of the things that I learned,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.18,0:03:51.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}至少是关于历史的进程的部分\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}at least about the history and the progress,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.32,0:03:53.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 也会得出一部分结论\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and of course, some of the conclusions as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.49,0:03:57.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我在简介里也列出了这些主题的快速链接 以及这个视频的文章版本\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}And I've got quick links to these topics and an article version of this video in the description too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.92,0:04:00.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好了 在一开始的时候 我需要澄清一件事\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Okay, right off the bat, we've gotta make one thing clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.76,0:04:04.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA和SpaceX不是竞争对手\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA and SpaceX are not competitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.74,0:04:07.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果你喜欢SpaceX 你应该为此感谢NASA\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}If you love SpaceX, you can thank NASA for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.80,0:04:11.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA是SpaceX最大的客户和它的支持者\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA is SpaceX's biggest customer and their biggest supporter,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.96,0:04:13.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以要记住这点\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}so let's keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.16,0:04:15.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好像这件事现在已经不是很明显了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}As if that wasn't obvious now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.82,0:04:19.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA简直是为了阿尔忒弥斯计划才投资的Starship\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}that NASA is literally investing in Starship for the Artemis program
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.25,0:04:25.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还能看到NASA为了商业载人计划在SpaceX的猎鹰9号火箭上涂装着它的标志\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and seeing NASA plastered all over SpaceX's Falcon 9 rocket for the Commercial Crew Program,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.23,0:04:30.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA和SpaceX的关系始于SpaceX刚开始的时候\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the relationship with NASA and SpaceX goes back to pretty much the beginning of SpaceX.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.80,0:04:31.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是指 毕竟\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}I mean, after all,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.68,0:04:37.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果不是NASA一开始为猎鹰9号和龙飞船投入了接近4亿美元\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}if it weren't for NASA's initial investment of nearly $400 million for the Falcon 9 and Dragon capsule,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.61,0:04:42.83,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}再加上商业补给服务和商业载人合同\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}then plus the multi-billion dollars for the CRS and commercial crew contracts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.95,0:04:46.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可以肯定地是 SpaceX达不到今天的高度\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}SpaceX most certainly wouldn't be where they are today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.34,0:04:47.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA确实在做着不可思议的工作\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA does incredible things,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.13,0:04:53.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}没有私人公司真的想做的重要的研究和科学\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}vital research and science that no private company would or really ever could do,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:57.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们在幕后做了很多常常被忽视的工作\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and they do a lot of behind the scenes things that can often go unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.86,0:05:00.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我的上一个对比SLS和Starship的视频在两年前\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}In my last video that compared SLS and Starship two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.78,0:05:05.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还是那个Tim难以理解地穿着俄罗斯高空服在他的卧室(做节目)的时光里\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}back in the Tim inexplicably wore a high altitude Russian flight suit in his bedroom days,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.92,0:05:13.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我真的在钻研为什么拿NASA这个组织直接和SpaceX这个私人公司对比并不公平\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}I really drilled into why it's not fair to compare NASA the organization directly to SpaceX, the private company.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.71,0:05:15.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你也许知道 一般情况下\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}As you probably know, in general,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.27,0:05:19.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我希望合作探索太空 并且支持我的观众反对那种党争\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}I'm team space and I like to encourage my audience to fight tribalism,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.65,0:05:23.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时不要老觉得只有一个方案是最佳的 其他都特别差\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and not just think one thing is the best and therefore everything else sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.93,0:05:28.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 当这个话题转到NASA建造并运营一个火箭的时候\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}But when it comes to NASA building and operating a rocket,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.86,0:05:33.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么我们能恰当地比较两个系统的好处和坏处\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}then we can properly compare the pros and cons of those two systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.59,0:05:35.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为我已经知道很多观众\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Because I already know there's plenty of you out there that are,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.86,0:05:39.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在说{\i1}橙色的火箭差(SLS) 闪亮的火箭好(Starship){\i0} 或者相反的话\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4\i1}Orange rocket bad, Shiny rocket good{\i0} and vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.70,0:05:42.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么让我们先和和稀泥\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}So let's come together, sing kumbaya a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.72,0:05:49.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}庆祝下我们已经有了多个超重型火箭了 没错\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and celebrate the fact that we have multiple mega rockets in existence, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.60,0:05:51.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好吧 既然已经没有了牵手的余地了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Okay, now that the hand-holding's out of the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.21,0:05:54.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}让我们定义一下超重型火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}let's define the term super heavy-lift launch vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.26,0:05:57.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你知道为什么没有在对比里包含像蓝色起源即将发布的新格伦火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}So you know why we're not including rockets like Blue Origin's upcoming New Glenn
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.10,0:06:00.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或者其他重型火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}or other heavy-lift launchers in this comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:04.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}航天业认为一个超重型火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The aerospace industry considers a super heavy-lift launcher
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.44,0:06:08.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}应该能将超过50吨载荷送入轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}as a rocket that can carry more than 50 tons into orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.71,0:06:11.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}超重型火箭当然可以把更大的东西送入轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Super heavy-lift launchers can of course put bigger things into orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.90,0:06:17.63,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这里面真正的含义是有着把更大的东西送入月球的潜力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}but what that really means is having enough capability to potentially send large things to the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.88,0:06:23.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或者让探测器知道外太阳系而不需要花时间的重力助推\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}or get probes on direct trajectories to our outer solar system without time-consuming gravity assists,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.91,0:06:27.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这可能让探测器进入外太阳系目的地的速度快3倍\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}potentially getting to outer solar system destinations almost three times faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.15,0:06:31.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}历史上 只有5个超重型火箭发射过\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Historically, there's only been five super heavy-lift launchers to ever fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.99,0:06:35.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而只有4个是成功的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and only four of those were actually successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:37.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们是(近地)运力达到140吨的土星五号\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}They're the Saturn V, which could lift 140 tons,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.97,0:06:42.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}苏联的失败的N-1火箭可以运载95吨\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the Soviet Union's unsuccessful N-I that could have lifted 95 tons,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.18,0:06:47.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后是苏联飞过两次的能源火箭能够运载100吨\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}then there's also the Soviet Union's twice-flown Energia rocket which could fly 100 tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.44,0:06:50.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SpaceX公司的重型猎鹰技术上可以运载约64吨\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}SpaceX's Falcon Heavy technically can loft about 64 tons
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.81,0:06:53.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在这种情况下三个助推器(两个助推器/一个芯一级)无法回收\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}if SpaceX chose to expend all three boosters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.99,0:06:57.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}虽然这从来没发生过也可能永远不会发生\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Although this has never happened and may never happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.41,0:07:01.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它确实让重型猎鹰变成了超重型运载火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}it does make Falcon Heavy technically a super heavy-lift launch vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.48,0:07:03.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管 当三个一级火箭都回收使用的时候\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Although, when all three cores are reused,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.51,0:07:06.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它的运载能力大概有30吨\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}its payload capability is more like 30 tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.55,0:07:08.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最后 则是航天飞机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}And lastly, the Space Shuttle which,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.03,0:07:11.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果你把航天飞机的轨道器作为它的有效载荷的一部分\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}if you include the orbiter as part of its payload capability,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.19,0:07:14.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它技术上可以把122.5吨送入轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}it could technically put 122.5 tons into orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.60,0:07:17.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也许需要马上指出的是 用同样的逻辑\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}I should probably point out real quick, by that same logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.15,0:07:21.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果包括了SLS的芯级\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}if you included, say, the core stage of the SLS,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.16,0:07:23.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在一定的配置下 它也是能入轨的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which can get into orbit if they wanted it to,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.91,0:07:28.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}按照这种说法 会使得它的有效载荷能力增加80吨\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}that would in that same way add another 80 tons to its payload capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.23,0:07:30.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是航天飞机跟这个不同\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}But the Shuttle was just a different beast,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.23,0:07:35.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}某种程度上需要把轨道器当作入轨的有效载荷\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and you kind of in some ways had to factor in the orbiter as payload that went orbital,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.71,0:07:40.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但实际上 可以部署的有效载荷质量真的只有大概27吨\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}but the actual, deployable payload capacity was really only about 27 tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.03,0:07:45.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管有太空梭C方案可以让它变为超重型火箭 但是 好吧(笑)\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Although there was a proposed shuttle C to make it super heavy, but, okay (chuckles)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.95,0:07:47.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}跑题了 我们继续吧\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}tangent, let's keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.26,0:07:49.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果人类想要尽快地返回月球\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}So if humans are to return to the moon ASAP,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.59,0:07:52.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或者说是要前往火星\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}or especially if we're to get to Mars,
