Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.43,0:08:01.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 这些任务都是我们期待已久的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Of course, I think we're long overdue for these kinds of missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.13,0:08:05.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我想让人类以4K的画质重返月球\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}I want humans on the moon again, in 4k!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.65,0:08:08.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}实际上 用8K也没问题\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Actually, let's make is 8k.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.04,0:08:11.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只要把MKBHD和他的相机送到那里\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Let's just send MKBHD up there with some of his cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.87,0:08:14.88,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在我们开始讲关于SLS和Starship的事实之前\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Now before we get started with SLS and Starship facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.88,0:08:17.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}万一你是真的两耳不闻窗外事\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}in case you've been living under a rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.00,0:08:21.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA正在致力于通过阿尔忒弥斯计划重返月球\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}we are currently working on getting back to the moon with NASA's Artemis program,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.80,0:08:27.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}大量的工作 资金和目标都展开了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and a substantial amount of work, funds and goals have been laid out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.49,0:08:30.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以在这个视频里 你会听到许多阿尔忒弥斯的名字\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}So during this video you'll hear Artemis thrown around quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.51,0:08:35.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管我们也可以把月球轨道门户这个绕月空间站和阿尔忒弥斯混在一起讲\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Although we could lump in the upcoming Space Station around the moon, Gateway, into Artemis,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.84,0:08:40.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是这期只关注SLS火箭和猎户座飞船\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}we're really just going to focus on the SLS rocket, the Orion capsule,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:41.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有载人着陆系统\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and the Human Lander System.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.84,0:08:47.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}毋庸置疑的是 SLS对于阿尔忒弥斯计划的地位相当于土星五号对阿波罗计划的地位\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Which to be clear, SLS is to Artemis as Saturn V was to the Apollo program.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.26,0:08:50.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而现在 月球轨道门户将不会参与到最初的一到两次载人登月当中\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}And right now, the Gateway is being skipped for the first crewed lunar landing or two
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.23,0:08:54.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而尽管很多事情都在为月球轨道门户酝酿和进行中\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and although a lot of things are drawn up and in progress for Gateway,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.73,0:08:59.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们只关注于月球着陆以及直接为此开发的设备\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}we're just going to focus on landing on the moon and the hardware that's directly involved in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.63,0:09:08.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在对比两个火箭之前 要先澄清一些事实\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}We're gonna set some records straight here before we pit these two rockets head-to-head,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.52,0:09:11.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为我觉得很多人有错误的看法\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}because I think a lot of people have the wrong idea
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.36,0:09:15.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在NASA怎么以及为什么一开始就追求SLS和猎户座的方案\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}when it comes to how and why NASA pursued SLS and Orion in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.41,0:09:17.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以及这是如何融入到阿尔忒弥斯计划中的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and how they fit into the Artemis program.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.68,0:09:19.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在哥伦比亚航天飞机(2003)的惨剧之后\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}After the Space Shuttle Columbia tragedy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.62,0:09:21.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA开始重新思考它的下一步计划\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA started to rethink it's next steps
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.80,0:09:25.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并且开始寻求一个能替代航天飞机的近地轨道(航天器)的方案\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and began looking to a low Earth orbit replacement to the shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.44,0:09:28.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并且开始决定要进行深空探测\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and also started to set its sights on deep space exploration
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.56,0:09:31.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为了做到这些 需要建造一个大火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and needed to build a big rocket in order to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.93,0:09:34.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA最初的版本是星座计划\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA's original vision was the Constellation program,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.02,0:09:37.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是一个替代航天飞机的载人运输系统\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which would be a crew transportation replacement for the Shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.68,0:09:41.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就是战神一火箭 还有一个深空版叫战神五火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}with the Ares I and a new deep space rocket called Ares V.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.03,0:09:47.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在2009年Augustine委员会报告指出这个项目的缓慢进度和巨大超支之后\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}After slow progress and massive cost overruns pointed out in the 2009 Augustine Commission report,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.49,0:09:50.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}星座计划最终取消了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the Constellation program wound up being canceled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.16,0:09:55.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以 2010年NASA授权法案指导NASA开发太空发射系统(SLS)\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}So the NASA Authorization Act of 2010 directed NASA to develop a Space Launch System
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.36,0:10:01.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SLS可以写到70到100吨的载荷到近地轨道 而改进版可达130吨以上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}capable of lifting 70 to 100 tons to low Earth orbit and evolvable to 130 tons or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.76,0:10:04.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}火箭必须能够发射猎户座载人飞船\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The vehicle must be able to lift the Orion Crew Vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:06.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为它的发展到目前为止就是为了配合猎户座飞船\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}since its development was so far along
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.00,0:10:11.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有就是NASA被要求尽可能地和现有的伙伴进行合作\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and NASA was required to work with existing partners when available.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.55,0:10:12.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们知道 NASA\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}As we know, NASA,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.91,0:10:15.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}没有把战神一火箭当作近地轨道的火箭进行使用\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}instead of an Ares 1 low Earth orbit vehicle,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.57,0:10:18.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而是最后通过商业伙伴对国际空间站进行货物运输\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}ended up hiring commercial partners to send cargo
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.40,0:10:21.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最终将会转变为通过商业载人计划对国际空间站进行载人运输\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and eventually crew to the ISS with the Commercial Crew Program,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.67,0:10:26.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而NASA的工作则是建造更为专一性的火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and NASA was tasked with a more focused and leaner rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.00,0:10:29.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这个想法是更快更有效地推出大型火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The thought was to roll out a massive rocket quickly and efficiently,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.96,0:10:38.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}正如指示中所要求的那样 需要在2016年12月31日之前开始运营这枚火箭(笑哭)\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}as their directive required the vehicle to be operational by December 31st, 2016. (chuckles) (sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.87,0:10:41.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA进行了品质因数的分析\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA performed a figures of merit analysis
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:44.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并把范围缩小到5种不同的火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and narrowed it down to five different variations of a launch vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.38,0:10:46.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有些看起来很不错\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Some of them were getting pretty exciting,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.41,0:10:51.83,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}譬如10米宽的芯级直径和富氧预燃分级燃烧循环发动机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}with a 10-meter wide core diameter and oxygen-rich staged combustion engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.83,0:10:57.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}分析对这些选项的评估指标为 55%的(可负担的)价格因素 25%的时间因素\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The analysis weighed the options of affordability being 55%, schedule 25%,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.74,0:11:00.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}10%的性能因素 10%的可行性因素\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}performance 10% and programmatic 10%.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:04.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA最终把项目落实为SLS\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA landed on what we now know as the SLS,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:07.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}虽然SLS和战神五号看起来非常像\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and although SLS and Ares V look very similar,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.84,0:11:11.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但实际上SLS是相当于从头设计\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}SLS was actually a fairly blank slate design,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.67,0:11:15.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是它肯定从DIRECT那个火箭方案上借鉴了不少东西\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}but it definitely took cues from a rocket proposal called DIRECT
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.31,0:11:21.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就意味着SLS肯定将严重依赖于航天飞机遗留下来的部件和设施\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}in which SLS would lean heavily on the literal leftover parts and facilities from the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:26.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}作为一个快速简便的方法 通过建造原型的方法来试验有史以来建造的最强大的火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}as a quick and easy way to prototype and test out the most powerful rocket ever built.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.16,0:11:29.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}和我们今天所知的商业载人计划不同\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Unlike the Commercial Crew Program we know today,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.43,0:11:32.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA将继续和航天飞机的承包商们一起合作\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA would continue to work with the contractors from the Shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.58,0:11:36.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}使用熟悉的成本加成合同的拨款方案\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}using the familiar cost-plus contracting funding scheme
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.36,0:11:40.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就基本意味着 {\i1}我们给你这些钱{\i0} 你把它给我搞定\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which basically means, {\i1}Here's how much money{\i0} we're going to give you to get it done,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.36,0:11:44.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4\i1}但是我们也会接受那些账单{\i0} 当预算超支的时候\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4\i1}but we'll also pick up the bill{\i0} on anything that goes over budget.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.36,0:11:49.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2011年以来SLS每年的拨款都在15亿美元左右\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}With funding hovering around 1.5 billion for SLS development per year since 2011
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.65,0:11:53.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有每年超过10亿美元多一点的猎户座飞船\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and the Orion Capsule receiving a little more than one billion a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.57,0:11:57.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}确保承包商有很多的资源来实现它们\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the contractors were assured to have plenty of resources to make it happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.31,0:12:01.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但同时是在不超出NASA实际预算范围的情况下\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}but while staying within a realistic NASA budget
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.55,0:12:04.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是和航天飞机时代的预算水准持平\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which matched the funding levels during the Shuttle era.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.49,0:12:06.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但伴随着成本加成合同的问题则是\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}But the problem with cost-plus contracting is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.44,0:12:13.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它很难激励承包商不超支 尤其是不超时\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}it offers very little incentive to remain on budget or especially on schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.25,0:12:18.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}事实上 不按时完成计划意味着承包商能拿到更多钱\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}In fact, timeline slips literally means more money for the contractors,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.37,0:12:20.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有SLS的主承包商\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and the prime contractor for SLS,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.25,0:12:24.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是波音将会为这个项目收到最多的钱\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Boeing, set to receive the most money for the project.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.00,0:12:27.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}虽然NASA给它的承包商进行了绩效评价\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Although NASA does performance reviews of their contractors,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.66,0:12:31.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对于某些承包商而言 这种仔细审查还是容易了一些\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}they've been scrutinized for being too easy on some of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.35,0:12:32.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}之后再说这件事\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}more on that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.52,0:12:37.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以 为了让一些承包商 员工 还有国会议员们开心\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}So in order to keep some of those contractors, employees, and members of congress happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.55,0:12:40.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}让火箭的遗产与航天飞机紧密联系在一起\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}keeping the rocket's heritage close to the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.20,0:12:46.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}至少是这么想的 这样就会确保资金还是会继续会拨给航天飞机的承包商\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}ensured that funds would continue to be appropriated to Shuttle contractors, or so the thought was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.41,0:12:51.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此尽管SLS确实看起来像是个巨型的没有机翼的航天飞机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}So although SLS does literally seem like a giant wingless space shuttle,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.49,0:12:55.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是火箭还是进行了若干提高性能的改进\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}it's actually had many changes to make the vehicle have higher performance
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.61,0:12:58.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时它会比航天飞机的零件成本低\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and lower costs than Space Shuttle's parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.30,0:13:00.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}接下来会快速概括它的改进\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Here's a quick rundown on the changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.41,0:13:02.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SLS会有一个五段的固体火箭助推器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The SLS will have five-segment solid rocket boosters,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.73,0:13:06.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而不是航天飞机使用的四段的那种\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}as opposed to the four-segment SRBs the Space Shuttle had,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.04,0:13:09.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时也没有任何用于回收的设备 以及一个重新设计过的塞子\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}lacking any recovery hardware and featuring a redesigned plug
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.90,0:13:11.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}让碎屑出来\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}that keeps squirrels and stuff out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:18.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}重新设计后 碎屑不会在点火时伤害到RS-25的喷管\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}with the redesign ensuring debris won't potentially damage the nearby RS-25 nozzles on ignition.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.33,0:13:22.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}芯一级 虽然看起来像是航天飞机的外储罐\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The core stage, which, although it looks like a Space Shuttle's external fuel tank,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.54,0:13:29.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}实际上除了颜色和8.4m直径以外 就没什么共同点了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}there's virtually nothing in common with the external fuel tank other than its color and its 8.4-meter diameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.66,0:13:32.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它采用了全新的铝材 AL 2219\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}It uses a new aluminum, AL 2219,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.90,0:13:35.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不同的结构和焊接技术\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}different construction and welding techniques,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.01,0:13:37.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}甚至不同的喷涂泡沫\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and even a different spray foam.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.47,0:13:41.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}人们肯定倾向于认为这只是个拉长的外储罐\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}People definitely tend to think it's literally a stretched external fuel tank,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.47,0:13:45.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这也包括我 但再说下 这之中真的完全不一样\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}me included, but again, it shares almost nothing in common,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.43,0:13:50.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这主要是因为SLS的罐顶承受来自上方的结构负载\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}mostly because SLS will have structural loads going down through the top of the tank
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.40,0:13:52.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而不是(航天飞机外储罐那样)承受侧面的负载\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}as opposed to hanging off the side of the tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.64,0:13:55.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而RS-25自从航天飞机时代以来 已经改进了不少\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The RS-25s have been tweaked quite a bit since the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.47,0:14:02.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们增加了推力 从104.5%到109% 在紧急情况下甚至能达到111%\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and have increased their power output from 104. 5% to 109%, or 111% in an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.95,0:14:05.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但同样 就像固体助推器一样\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}But again, just like the SRBs,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.62,0:14:12.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SLS上的RS-25D和以后的RS-25E衍生型当然不会进行回收\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the RS-25D and later the RS-25E variants will of course not be recovered on SLS.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.83,0:14:13.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}顺便提个有趣的东西\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Just a fun side note,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.70,0:14:19.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些数字都是基于原来的海平面额定推力1600kN计算而来\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}those percentage numbers are based on the original rated thrust of 1.6 meganewtons at sea level.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.44,0:14:22.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在航天飞机主发动机的一些改进之后\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}After some tweaks in the Space Shuttle's main engines,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.12,0:14:26.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们最终能超出航天飞机时期的原本的设计推力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}they wound up being able to be throttled up beyond their original design during the Shuttle's program
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:29.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并且在SLS时期更进一步\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and are being pushed even further with SLS.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.14,0:14:32.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}另外一个节省资金 加速计划的决定是\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Another cost-saving and timeline-helping decision
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.70,0:14:39.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SLS一开始就用几乎是ULA的Delta 4和Delta 4重型火箭的上面级\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}was to initially fly the SLS with quite literally the upper stage from ULA's Delta IV and Delta IV Heavy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.24,0:14:42.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是Delta低温二级 或者说DCSS\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}known as the Delta Cryogenic Second Stage, or DCSS,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.28,0:14:47.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只不过进行了修改来搭配在8.5米宽的芯级上面\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}only it's been modified to fit on top of the 8.5-meter wide core stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.72,0:14:51.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有着不同的氢气罐 和更多的RCS(反推力系统)燃料\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}have different hydrogen tanks, and more reaction control fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.52,0:14:56.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这种配置被称为临时低温推进分级 或者说ICPS\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}This configuration is known as the Interim Cryogenic Propulsion Stage, or ICPS.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.67,0:15:02.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SLS计划有一个更强的上面级叫做探索上面级\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}SLS is intended to have a much more powerful upper stage known as Exploration Upper Stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.36,0:15:08.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这被认为是SLS Block 1B的升级部分 让SLS的运载能力更为强大\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which is considered to be part of the Block 1B upgrade and makes SLS much more capable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.34,0:15:10.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}接下来 我们需要说说猎户座飞船\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Next, we need to talk about the Orion capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.12,0:15:13.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在阿尔忒弥斯任务中 它位于整个火箭的最顶端\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}It sits on top of this whole vehicle for the Artemis missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.11,0:15:16.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}猎户座飞船是一个相当传统的载人飞船\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The Orion Capsule is a fairly traditional crew capsule
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.88,0:15:21.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在某种程度上 它只是一个放大的新版阿波罗飞船\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and in some ways is a newer and embiginated version of the Apollo capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:24.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 尽管看起来类似\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}But although it looks quite similar,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.82,0:15:27.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它比看上去要大得多\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}it's a lot bigger than it might appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.38,0:15:31.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}直径上面 对比阿波罗的3.9米 它有5米\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}At five meters wide versus the Apollo capsule's 3.9 meters wide,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.43,0:15:34.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}达到了很不错的9立方米的容积\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and sporting an impressive nine cubic meters of volume,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.72,0:15:41.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对比阿波罗飞船的6.2立方米 这个空间挺大的 能够容纳6个宇航员\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}compared to 6.2 cubic meters, it'll be quite a bit roomier and capable of up to six astronauts,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.32,0:15:46.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管对于阿尔忒弥斯任务而言 它只会携带4名宇航员 而阿波罗只带了三个\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}although it'll probably only fly four for the Artemis missions, versus Apollo's three,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.04,0:15:49.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不过阿波罗技术上能带5个宇航员\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which could technically fit five.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.33,0:15:50.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好吧 很勉强\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Well, barely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.69,0:15:53.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}猎户座以前曾被称为载人探索飞行器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The Orion capsule used to be called the Crew Exploration Vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.94,0:15:56.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是它在星座计划时期研发中的名字\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}when it was in development for the Constellation program.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.09,0:16:00.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是它已经改变了不少 并且拥有另一个节省成本的措施\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}But it has changed quite a bit and now features another cost savings measure,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.43,0:16:04.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就是基于欧空局的自动运载飞船改进而来的服务舱\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which is a service module based on ESA's Automated Transfer Vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.58,0:16:07.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 我们仍需要提到一个这批航天器中的新东西\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}But one thing we need to mention that's still new to this whole line-up,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.31,0:16:08.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且仍在研发中的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and it's still in progress,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.97,0:16:12.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对于阿尔忒弥斯计划着陆于月球上而言绝对是需要的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and is definitely required for the Artemis program to land on the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.99,0:16:16.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}实际上那就是月球着陆器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and that is of course the actual lunar lander.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.71,0:16:18.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这也就是今天这个主题的来源\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}And that brings us to today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.27,0:16:20.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}到目前为止 我们所讨论过的东西\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}So far, everything we've talked about and discussed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.55,0:16:25.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只是通过SLS和猎户座飞船载人抵达绕月轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}is only capable of getting humans into lunar orbit with SLS and Orion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.48,0:16:31.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SLS Block 1还没有能力一块儿将月球着陆器带过去\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}because there really still isn't the capability to also carry up a lunar lander with SLS Block 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.31,0:16:34.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}甚至是升级版的Block 1B\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}or even the upgraded Block 1B.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.23,0:16:39.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 NASA已经为阿尔忒弥斯计划正式选择了三个非常 非常不同的月球着陆器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}But NASA has officially selected three very, very different lunar landers for the Artemis program,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.85,0:16:46.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且每个提供商都需要在2021年前拟定它们的着陆器前往月球的方法\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and each one has until 2021 to draw up exactly how they'll get their landers to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.27,0:16:48.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你知道的 有些方案可能最终会\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}You know some proposals could actually wind up
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.19,0:16:53.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}使用升级版的SLS也就是Block 1B来和猎户座一起发射它们的登月舱\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}still sending modules alongside Orion in the upgraded Block 1B SLS.
